data.chText: 首要的；最著名的；最成功的；第一的

data.enText: one of the country's premier chefs
used especially in newspapers, etc. to mean ‘prime minister’
(in Canada) the first minister of a province or territory

tr: the person who is head of state (in several countries)
the person who holds the position of head of the government in the United Kingdom
perform a work for the first time
be performed for the first time
example: We premiered the opera of the young composer and it was a critical success

value.def: The leader of the government of a country is sometimes referred to as the country's premier .

example.tran: 澳大利亚总理保罗·基廷

value.def: Premier is used to describe something that is considered to be the best or most important thing of a particular type.

example.tran: 这个国家的顶尖歌剧团

value.tran: 最好的；最佳的；最重要的
